        <h2 class="mb-3">About Gigantic & Modding</h2>

        <p>
            Gigantic (2017) is a hero-based action game that focuses on fast-paced team combat
            and unique character abilities. Even though the game is no longer officially active,
            it still has a small dedicated community of players.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h5>Why Modding Matters</h5>
        <p>
            Modding allows players to improve balance, fix bugs, and enhance gameplay systems
            that are no longer updated by any developers.
        </p>

        <h5>What I Mod</h5>
        <ul>
            <li>Hero balance adjustments (damage, cooldowns, scaling)</li>
            <li>Bug fixes (ability interactions, status effects)</li>
            <li>Gameplay feel improvements (end lag, responsiveness)</li>
            <li>Experimental reworks of abilities</li>
        </ul>

        <h5>Tools & Approach</h5>
        <p>
            I focus on analyzing game behavior and adjusting values to improve fairness and playability
            while keeping the original identity of the game intact.
            It lets me improve a game I already love and fix numerous issues that have been left unaddressed for years.
        </p>

